From: crackerjacques <jack@supremeoverlordjabs.co>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 12:10:00 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: rk3308: support the RK3308B codec variant

The driver rejects chip version B (RK3308B, GRF chip id 0x3308) with
-EINVAL during probe, even though the rest of the driver already copes
with it: the version checks only special-case ACODEC_VERSION_C (the
BS-style DAC mode/IO register layout and the version-C digital volume
registers), so version B takes the same paths as version A - which is
exactly what the Rockchip vendor driver does for this part.

Drop the early return so the RK3308B internal codec probes. Tested on a
Luckfox Nova (RK3308B): the card registers ("Found codec version B") and
capture from the on-board mic works.

Signed-off-by: crackerjacques <jack@supremeoverlordjabs.co>
---
 sound/soc/codecs/rk3308_codec.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/sound/soc/codecs/rk3308_codec.c
+++ b/sound/soc/codecs/rk3308_codec.c
@@ -854,7 +854,7 @@
 		break;
 	case 0x3308:
 		rk3308->codec_ver = ACODEC_VERSION_B;
-		return dev_err_probe(rk3308->dev, -EINVAL, "Chip version B not supported\n");
+		break;
 	case 0x3308c:
 		rk3308->codec_ver = ACODEC_VERSION_C;
 		break;
